An additional dam will be constructed at the Seven Forks hydropower dams in Embu and Machakos counties.Energy CS Charles Keter (pictured) on Friday said the new dam will be 129m high and will be built at Masinga to increase water volume in the dam to generate more power. He said machinery will be added at the power stations in the dams on the River Tana. Keter visited the dams to check on water levels.